Analysis pipeline (script whose names begin with '_' are not needed ones):
==================================================================================================================
-   submit_count.sh : align all the sequencing reads onto a reference using CellRanger. Remember sample names 
                      should not contain string '_S', as '_S' usually represents sample names.
-   move_cellranger_outs.R : move the Seurat-demanded files generated by CellRanger
-       from the directory of samples to a specified directory
-   1_load_count_data.rmd : load samples into a SeuratObject
-   2_quality_control.rmd : perform quality control (QC) according to the amount of
       ribosomal RNAs, mito RNAs, and mRNAs, etc.
-   3_integration.rmd : integrate multiple samples saved in Seurat Objects
-   4_cell_type_annotation.rmd : annotate the cell types
-   5_DEG_analysis.rmd : differential expression analysis
-   6_subtyping.rmd : subdivide one important cluster into several subclusters and generate UMAPs
-   _7_cell_type_specific_genes.rmd : include loading data, integration, cell type annotation, extracting 
        cell-type-specific genes, generating heatmaps and circular plots. This is
        a combination of multiple scripts.
-   _8_extract_cell_types.R : extract interested cell types using their names, which is always conducted
        when running CellChat
-   9_transform_data.R : TBD
-   10_transform_data.R : 
-   11_chord.R : 
-   12_circos.rmd : 
==================================================================================================================
